<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1059,1428,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">
Before 1962, this species had been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[645,733,1428,1450]" name="Slovakia" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
only at 9 identified localities (
<bibRefCitation author="PUNGUR J" box="[159,307,1457,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref3823" refString="PUNGUR J. (1899): Ordo Orthoptera. Fauna Regni Hungariae III. Arthropoda. - Societas scientiarum naturalium hungarica, Budapest: 1 - 16." type="book chapter" year="1899">PUNGUR 1899</bibRefCitation>
, SCHNEEBERG 1931, 
<bibRefCitation author="GULICKA J" box="[533,689,1457,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453" pagination="617 - 630" refId="ref2838" refString="GULICKA J. (1954): Prispevok k rozsireniu Orthopter a Dermapter na Slovensku. (Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Verbreitung einiger Orthopteren und Dermapteren in der Slowakei). - Biologia, Bratislava 9: 617 - 630. [in Slovak with German summary]." type="journal article" year="1954">GULIČKA 1954</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="GULICKA J" box="[704,757,1457,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453" pagination="41 - 61" refId="ref2887" refString="GULICKA J. (1967): Orthoptera, Blattodea, Mantodea, Dermaptera zatopoveho uzemia pod Vihorlatom. (Orthoptera, Blattodea, Mantodea, Dermaptera des Inundationsgebietes unter dem Vihorlat). - Acta Fac. Rer. natur. Univ. Comen., Zool. 12: 41 - 61. [in Slovak with German summary]." type="journal article" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="MARAN J" box="[772,917,1457,1479]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453" pagination="132 - 139" refId="ref3652" refString="MARAN J. (1954): Rovnokridly hmyz statnich prirodnich rezervaci v okoli Sturova na jiznim Slovensku. (Die Orthopterenfauna der staatlichen Naturschutzgebiete bei Sturovo in der Sudslowakei). - Ochrana prirody 9: 132 - 139. [in Czech with German summary]." type="journal article" year="1954">MAŘAN 1954</bibRefCitation>
). Until 2000, there were no further published data on its occurrence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1058,1523,1601]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1059,210,316]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="454" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">
In 2000-2006 suitable localities were mapped more intensively, and we found this species at 35 localities (we confirmed pre-1962 findings in three localities). Summarizing all known published and our unpublished data, the species had been found in a total of 41 localities in 29 squares of the Slovak Fauna Databank (6.7 % of all squares, 
<figureCitation box="[988,1054,210,232]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[151,184,1418,1438]" captionTargetBox="[152,1055,892,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-63@7.[151,1058,892,1407]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4: Distribution of Aiolopus thalassinus in Slovakia in mapping squares of the Slovak Fauna Databank (for explanation, see Fig. 1)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5409792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5409792/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, Appendix 2). Like the previous species, the increase in known localities is more probably the result of intensive research being carried out at dusk, when this species is most active (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="GULICKA J" box="[190,336,294,316]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" pagination="617 - 630" refId="ref2838" refString="GULICKA J. (1954): Prispevok k rozsireniu Orthopter a Dermapter na Slovensku. (Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Verbreitung einiger Orthopteren und Dermapteren in der Slowakei). - Biologia, Bratislava 9: 617 - 630. [in Slovak with German summary]." type="journal article" year="1954">GULIČKA 1954</bibRefCitation>
) than an indication of a northward spread (
<bibRefCitation author="KRISTIN A &amp; KANUCH P" box="[752,943,294,316]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" refId="ref3609" refString="KRISTIN A., KANUCH P. &amp; M. SAROSSY (2007): Did the northern range of distribution of two tropical Orthopterans (Insecta) change recently? - Polish Journal of Ecol. 55 (in press)." type="book" year="2007">KRIŠTÍN et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
